cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on using deep convolutional neural networks (CNN) to improve the performance of face anti-spoofing, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the supervised learning approach used to train the CNN, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves some data pre-processing techniques, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method on two challenging datasets, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
